node.title: Victoria records 1,029 new COVID-19 cases and three deaths
node.description: There are now 9,533 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 460 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,029\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and three\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 9,533\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 460\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.\u00a0", "There are 316\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 44\u00a0are in intensive care, and 23\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 54\u00a0people are in intensive care but their infections are no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 49,818\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,510\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has\u00a0fully vaccinated more than 89\u00a0per cent of its\u00a0population aged 12 and over.", "More to come.", "", "
